Index: =================================================================== --- +++ @@ -6,106 +6,9 @@ import ThebannerCom from "../components/ThebannerCom.vue"; import axios from 'axios'; export default { - components: { - ThebannerCom, - }, - data() { - return { - naturals:[], - title:'Natural ', - img: '../src/assets/image/Rectangle11.png', - imgs: '../src/assets/image/Group 40.png', - - allMenuItems: [ - { - id:1, - title: 'Tonle Sapt', - desc:"Tonlé Sap; Khmer: ទន្លេសាប, Tônlé Sab; lit. 'Fresh River' or commonly translated as 'Great Lake' is a lake in the northwest of Cambodia. Belonging to the Mekong River system, Tonlé Sap is the largest freshwater lake in Southeast Asia and one of the most diverse and productive ecosystems in the world.
Fish: Siamese mud carp, Snakehead murrel, Walking catfish, MORE
Area: 2,700 km²
Max. depth: 10 m (33 ft)
Cities: Krong Siem Reap, Krong Battambang
Length: 250 km
Basin countries: Cambodia
Coordinates: 12°53′N 104°04′E﻿ / ﻿12.883°N 104.067°E", - image: '../src/assets/image/natural/Rectangle33.png', - }, - { - id:2, - title: 'Battambang Bat Caves', - desc: "The Battambang Bat Caves offer an unforgettable experience for visitors to Cambodia. Located near the town of Battambang, these caves are home to millions of bats that create a breathtaking spectacle every evening as they emerge to hunt for food.
Millions of Bats: The main attraction is the sheer number of bats that inhabit the caves. As the sun begins to set, they emerge in a massive, swirling cloud, creating a truly awe-inspiring sight.
Phnom Sampov Mountain: The bat caves are located on Phnom Sampov Mountain, which also offers other points of interest like the Killing Caves, a dark chapter in Cambodia's history.
Best Time to Visit: The ideal time to witness the bat exodus is around sunset. Arrive early to secure a good viewing spot.
Local Community: The bat caves are a significant source of income for the local community, as bat guano is used as fertilizer.", - image: '../src/assets/image/natural/Rectangle 50.png', - }, - { - id:3, - title: 'Preah monivong bokor national park', - desc: "Preah Monivong Bokor National Park is a captivating destination for nature lovers and those seeking a glimpse into Cambodia's rich history. Nestled in the Damrei Mountains, this sprawling park offers stunning landscapes, intriguing historical sites, and a chance to escape the hustle and bustle of city life.
Highlights of Bokor National Park
  • Bokor Hill Station: This abandoned colonial hill station is a fascinating remnant of Cambodia's past. Explore the ruins of hotels, a casino, and a church, and imagine the grandeur of the era.

  • Stunning Views: The park is known for its breathtaking panoramas. From the summit of Phnom Bokor, you can enjoy sweeping vistas of the surrounding countryside, including the Gulf of Thailand on clear days.

  • Waterfall: While the waterfall might be dry during the dry season, the area around it is still a pleasant spot for a picnic or a leisurely stroll.

  • Wildlife: Although the park's wildlife is primarily elusive, there's a chance to spot various bird species and other animals.

  • Spiritual Retreat: The park is home to a Buddhist temple, offering a peaceful atmosphere for meditation and reflection.
    • ", - image: '../src/assets/image/natural/Rectangle35.png', - }, - { - id:4, - title: 'Koh Tonsay (Rabbit Island)', - desc: "Koh Tonsay, or Rabbit Island, is a charming escape from the mainland hustle. This small island, located off the coast of Kep, offers a laid-back atmosphere and stunning natural beauty.
  • Battambang Bat Caves: Known for the stunning spectacle of millions of bats emerging at sunset.

  • Preah Monivong Bokor National Park: A mountainous area offering historical ruins, beautiful scenery, and opportunities for hiking and exploring.

  • Koh Tonsay (Rabbit Island): A tropical island paradise with pristine beaches, ideal for relaxation and water activities.
    • ", - image: '../src/assets/image/natural/Rectangle36.png', - }, - { - id:5, - title: 'Phnum Aoral', - desc: "Phnom Aural, also spelled Phnom Aoral, is the tallest peak in Cambodia. It is 1,813 meters tall. It is in the eastern part of the Cardamom Mountains. To protect the biodiversity of the mountains, Phnom Aural Wildlife Sanctuary was established in 1993. This mountain in located in Aoral District, Kampong Speu Province.
  • Impressive height: Standing at 1,813 meters, it offers breathtaking views.

  • Biodiversity: Home to rare wildlife, including the Cambodian Laughingthrush.

  • Challenging hike: Reaching the summit requires physical fitness and endurance.

  • Protected area: The Phnom Aural Wildlife Sanctuary safeguards the mountain's unique ecosystem.
    • ", - image: '../src/assets/image/natural/Rectangle37.png', - }, - { - id:6, - title: 'Ream National Park', - desc: "Ream National Park is a diverse ecosystem located near Sihanoukville, Cambodia.
  • Terrestrial habitats: Forests, mangroves, and wetlands.

  • Marine life: Coral reefs, seagrass beds, and various aquatic species.

  • Wildlife: A variety of birds, mammals, and reptiles.
    • ", - image: '../src/assets/image/natural/Rectangle38.png', - }, - { - id:8, - title: 'Koh Rong Island', - desc: "Koh Rong is Cambodia's second-largest island, renowned for its pristine beaches, crystal-clear waters, and lush jungle. It's a popular destination for backpackers and those seeking a laid-back island escape.
  • Stunning beaches: Soft white sand and turquoise waters create a postcard-perfect setting.

  • Vibrant marine life: Excellent snorkeling and diving opportunities with colorful coral reefs.

  • Island exploration: Hike through the jungle, discover hidden waterfalls, and explore secluded coves.

  • Party atmosphere: Some areas offer lively nightlife and beach parties.

  • Relaxation: Unwind in beachfront bungalows and enjoy fresh seafood.
    • ", - image: '../src/assets/image/natural/Rectangle40.png', - }, - { - id:9, - title: 'Kirirom National Park', - desc: "Kirirom National Park, officially called Preah Suramarit-Kossamak Kirirom National Park, is a national park in Cambodia located in the eastern part of the Cardamom Mountains at a mean elevation of 675 m. It is Cambodia's first officially designated national park, that was established in 1993.
  • Area: 283.75 km2 (109.56 sq mi)

  • Pine forests: A unique landscape for the region, offering a cooler climate.

  • Biodiversity: Home to various plant and animal species, including birds.

  • Outdoor activities: Hiking, camping, and exploring waterfalls are popular.

  • Historical significance: The park has a rich history, with remnants of its past as a hill station.
    • ", - image: '../src/assets/image/natural/Rectangle41.png', - }, - { - id:10, - title: 'Bou Sra Waterfall', - desc: "Busra or Boo Sra Waterfall, is a scenic waterfall now located in Bousra Eco Park, Pech Chreada District, Mondulkiri Province, Cambodia, about 43 kilometers from the provincial town of Sen Monorom and just 15 kilometers from the Vietnamese border.
  • Triple-tiered cascade: The waterfall drops in three stages, creating a mesmerizing spectacle.

  • Surrounding natural beauty: Lush greenery and the refreshing atmosphere make it a perfect escape.

  • Popular tourist spot: Offers opportunities for swimming, picnicking, and photography.

  • Local charm: Immerse yourself in the local culture and enjoy the vibrant atmosphere.
    • ", - image: '../src/assets/image/natural/Rectangle42.png', - }, - { - id:11, - title: 'Phnom Khnang Phsar', - desc: "Khnong Phsar is a popular hiking destination in Cambodia, known for its:
  • Lush greenery: Offers stunning views of rolling hills and dense forests.

  • Hiking trails: Various difficulty levels cater to both beginners and experienced hikers.

  • Camping opportunities: Spend a night under the stars and immerse yourself in nature.

  • Eco-tourism: Promotes sustainable tourism and supports local communities.
    • ", - image: '../src/assets/image/natural/Rectangle43.png', - }, - { - id:12, - title: 'Phnom Kulen National Park', - desc: "Phnom Kulen National Park is a must-visit for anyone exploring Cambodia. This sacred mountain is believed to be the birthplace of the Khmer Empire.
    Highlights of Phnom Kulen:
  • Rich history: Learn about the origins of the Khmer Empire and its significance.

  • Natural beauty: Enjoy lush forests, cascading waterfalls, and stunning landscapes.

  • Archaeological wonders: Explore the River of a Thousand Lingas and the impressive reclining Buddha.

  • Outdoor activities: Hiking, swimming, and picnicking are popular options.
    • ", - image: '../src/assets/image/natural/Rectangle 68.png', - }, - { - id:13, - title: 'Virachey National Park', - desc: "Virachey National Park is Cambodia's largest protected area, offering a glimpse into the country's raw, natural beauty. Located in the northeast, it's renowned for its:
  • Vast and diverse ecosystems: From dense rainforests to open grasslands, the park supports a rich array of flora and fauna.

  • Endangered wildlife: Home to rare and threatened species, including the critically endangered Siamese crocodile.

  • Cultural significance: The park is inhabited by indigenous communities who have lived in harmony with the environment for centuries.

  • Adventure opportunities: Trekking, birdwatching, and exploring waterfalls are popular activities.
    • ", - image: '../src/assets/image/natural/Rectangle 69.png', - }, - - ], - } - }, - mounted() { - axios.get('http://localhost:8000/natural') - .then(res => { - this.naturals = res.data; - }) - .catch(error => { - console.error('There was an error:', error); - }); - }, - -}; +
